Product Description: The apple tree is a deciduous tree in the rose family best known for its sweet, pomaceous fruit, the apple.
Mangoes are juicy stone fruit from numerous species of tropical trees belonging to the flowering plant genus Mangifera, cultivated mostly for their edible fruit.
A grape is a fruit, botanically a berry, of the deciduous woody vines of the flowering plant genus Vitis.

Category Description: In everyday usage, vegetables are certain parts of plants that are consumed by humans as food as part of a savory meal.

Momordica charantia, known as bitter melon, bitter gourd, bitter squash, or balsam-pear, is a tropical and subtropical vine of the family Cucurbitaceae, widely grown in Asia, Africa, and the Caribbean for its edible fruit.
